definition.value: Fluorescent tag positive cell count is a cell counter result data that states the number of fluorescent tag positive cells that were counted in the cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
Fluorescent tag positive cell density is a cell counter result data that quantifies the number density of the fluorescent tag positive cells in the sample in the cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
A fluorescent tag positive percentage is a cell counter result datum that quantifies the percentage of fluorescent tag positive cells in the sample in the cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
A circularity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the two-dimensional roundness of an entity. [Allotrope]
A fluorescent tag identifier is an identifier for the type of molecules having the role of fluorescent tag. [Allotrope]
An analyte identifier is an identifier that identifies some material with the role of analyte. [Allotrope]
A mass chromatogram data cube is a data cube that is a representation of some mass chromatogram. [Allotrope]
A three-dimensional mass spectrum data cube is a data cube that is a representation of a three-dimensional mass spectrum. [Allotrope]
A peak assignment identifier is an identifier that identifies some material with the role of analyte that the peak is assigned to represent. [Allotrope]
A peak group identifier is an identifier that identifiers some peak group. [Allotrope]
A peak slope at start is a peak facet that denotes the slope of the baseline at the peak start. [Allotrope]

label.value: chromatographic peak resolution using Foley-Dorsey method

definition.value: A chromatographic peak resolution that is calculated using peak widths from the Foley Dorsey equation for asymmetric peaks. [Allotrope]

label.value: chromatographic peak resolution using peak widths at 4.4 % height

definition.value: A chromatographic peak resolution that is calculated using peak widths at 4.4 % peak height. [Allotrope]
A zeroth order raw moment is a descriptive statistic that denotes the area under the curve of a distribution. [Allotrope]
Kurtosis is a descriptive statistic that is a measure of the tailedness of a distribution. [Wikipedia]
A mass spectrum identifier is an identifier that identifies some mass spectrum. [Allotrope]
An ultraviolet-visible spectrum identifier is an identifier that identifies some ultraviolet-visible spectrum. [Allotrope]
A well plate identifier is an identifier that identifies some well plate. [Allotrope]
A calculated data aggregate document is a document that aggregates calculated data documents. [Allotrope]
A calculated data document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some calculation. [Allotrope]
A calculated data name is a written name that denotes the data output of some calculation. [Allotrope]
A calculated result is a mathematical object that is the data output of some calculation. [Allotrope]
A calculated data identifier is an identifier that identifies the data output of some calculation. [Allotrope]
A data source aggregate document is a document that aggregates data source documents. [Allotrope]
A data source document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some data with the role of data input. [Allotrope]
A data source identifier is an identifier that identifies some data with the role of data input. [Allotrope]
A processed data identifier is an identifier that identifies the data output of some data transformation.. [Allotrope]
A data source feature is a facet that defines the feature with the role of a description or classification of a property, characteristic or facet of some data with the role of data input. [Allotrope]
A qPCR aggregate document is a document that aggregates qPCR documents. [Allotrope]
A qPCR document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some qPCR experiment. [Allotrope]
A total cycle number setting is a control setting that specifies the number of cycles to run in some repeated process. [Allotrope]
A denaturing temperature setting is a temperature setting that specifies the intended temperature of some denaturing process. [Allotrope]
A denaturing duration setting is a duration setting that specifies the intended duration of some denaturing process. [Allotrope]
An annealing temperature setting is a temperature setting that specifies the intended temperature of some annealing process. [Allotrope]
An annealing duration setting is a duration setting that specifies the intended duration of some annealing process. [Allotrope]
A primer extension temperature setting is a temperature setting that specifies the intended temperature of some primer extension process. [Allotrope]
A primer extension duration setting is a duration setting that specifies the intended duration of some primer extension process. [Allotrope]
A genotyping qPCR method identifier is an identifier that identifies the method used for some genotyping qPCR experiment. [Allotrope]
A genotyping qPCR method setting is a control setting that specifies the threshold of some genotyping qPCR experiment. [Allotrope]
A genotyping qPCR result is an assay result that is output of a genotyping qPCR experiment. [Allotrope]
A reporter data cube is a data cube that represents a plot of reporter dye result against cycle. [Allotrope]
A passive reference dye data cube is a data cube that represents a plot of passive reference dye result against cycle. [Allotrope]
A melting curve data cube is a data cube that represents a plot of fluorescence against temperature. [Allotrope]
A reference DNA description is a description that describes the DNA target of a reference gene or endogenous control within the PCR experiment. [Allotrope]
A reference sample description is a description that describes some material with the role of reference sample. [Allotrope]
A first order raw moment is a descriptive statistic that denotes the mean of a distribution. [Allotrope]
An ASM conversion document is a data processing document that encompasses the information associated with an ASM conversion process. [Allotrope]
A group identifier is an identifier that identifies some collection or group. [Allotrope]
A solution analyzer aggregate document is a document that aggregates solution analyzer documents. [Allotrope]
A solution analyzer document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some solution analyzer run. [Allotrope]
